  "text": "Here S local cpu is the predicted CPU supply in cycles/sec available to the application. D local cpu is the predicted CPU demand in cycles required by the operation. The other terms represent the time taken for a remote execution(s): transmitting data to a server, receiving results from it, round trip time of one or more RPCs, and server-side computation. Network bandwidth and round trip time estimates are provided by the base Odyssey infrastructure [CITATION_1] . The predictor also computes the effects of VM paging and remote file access [CITATION_2] ; for brevity, we do not discuss these.",
